  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">SORUDA EFSVL Support to SSR in Lamwo</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">SORUDA intends to complement the UNHCR Programme of Refugee and Host-community Programme and Empowerment (REHOPE). It targets both the Refugee (70%) and Host-communities (30%) in Lamwo District areas of Lukung, Madi Opei, Agoro and Palabek (Ogili, Gem and Kal) inAcholi Sub-region.
In total, 1000 households will be targeted for Lamwo District.


Overall Goal: Contribute to #increased household food security among South Sudanese refugees (70%) and host communities (30%) in Lamwo District by August 2017#
Objectives (WASH, EFSVL, Protection)
1. To increase access to food among 500 households through cash for work initiative in Lamwo District by August2017.
2. To support 500 households with fast maturing agro-inputs and tools to meet their food needs in Lamwo District by August 2017
3. To build capacity of 500 individuals in energy saving techniques and environment conservation in Lamwo District by  August, 2017

1. EFSVL Outcomes
1.1 Increased employment opportunities and incomes for 500 households through cash for work initiatives.
2.1 Enhanced vegetable production among 500hh in refugee and host communities.
3.1Increased skills and knowledge in making Lorena stoves by refugees and host communities</narrative>
  </description>
